ZCZC EE53
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 222300 UTC
THIS PERIOD SHOULD START WITH HIGH PRESSURE DOMINANT OVER THE UK AND IRELAND
LYING CENTRED OVER SEERN ENGLAND WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE NEAR 1039. THIS FEATURE
CONNECTS TO THE AZORES HIGH WHILE LOW PRESSURE SYSTEMS ARE HELD AT SOME
DISTANCE TO THE N. TOWARDS THE MIDDLE OF THE WORKING WEEK A NEW DEEP LOW
IS EXP TO MOV EWARDS ACROSS ICELAND REACHING NORWEGIAN BASIN AND THEN SCANDINAVIA
THROUGH WEDNESDAY AS THE HIGH FURTHER S DECLINES. A SECOND LOW MAY FOLLOW
ON THE HEELS OF THE FIRST LOW LATER WEDNESDAY PERHAPS CROSSING THE FAEROES
AND NERN ISLES EWARDS LATER. THESE FEATURES MAY THEN AMALGAMATE AND FILL
IN THE VICINITY OF SCANDINAVIA TO END THE PERIOD FORMING A LARGE AND COMPLEX
LOW PRESSURE CENTRE HERE WITH THE MAIN HIGH HAVING RETROGRESSED INTO THE
MID-ATLANTIC. NO HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP IN NITON FOR MUCH OF THE PERIOD
BUT PERHAPS BRIEFLY STRG IN SHANNON THURSDAY
